      <h2 id="how-heading">What it is, and why it works</h2>
      <p>FPJ is a traditional fermented extract. Nutrient-dense plants — horsetail and nettle — are fermented with organic sugar, which draws their soluble nutrients and plant compounds into a stable, plant-available liquid.</p>
      <p>The ferment also carries IMO (indigenous microorganisms — the bacteria and fungi already adapted to local soils). Applied as a drench or foliar feed, it feeds the plant and inoculates the soil food web at the same time. That is the difference from a salt-based fertilizer: it feeds the biology that keeps feeding the plant.</p>
      <hr class="fpj-rule">
      <h3>Every ingredient, on the label</h3>
      <ul class="ingredients">
        <li>Horsetail</li>
        <li>Nettle</li>
        <li>Cannabis sativa</li>
        <li>Organic sugar</li>
        <li>Dechlorinated water</li>
        <li>IMO (indigenous microorganisms)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
